 the motivation for writing the works in question; its purpose; the role of the author, patrons and audiences; the choice of language and the reasons for that choice; the place of historical writing in the broader debate over the suitability of Persian for scholarly writing."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aHistoriographyzIranvEarly works to 1800. 0aHistoriographyzPersian Gulf Region. 0aIslamxHistoriographyvEarly works to 1800. 0aPersian philology. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aHISTORY / Historiography.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311078047540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447094040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474470940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474470940/original  a978-3-11-078047-5  Edinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK